The paper discusses the use of deep learning for image classification in echocardiograms, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of supervised learning and convolutional neural networks also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a likely sub-category. The paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for classification suggests neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as a possible sub-category.
